                            <comment id="12849433" author="pkamath" created="Wed, 24 Mar 2010 21:00:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached patch makes the required changes in TextLoader to use BZip2TextInputFormat if the load location ends with extension &quot;.bz&quot; or &quot;.bz2&quot; like PigStorage. Also for non bzip data, TextLoader will now use PigTextInputFormat rather than TextInputFormat so that input directories can be recursively traversed. I have also changed BZip2TextInputFormat to extend PigFileInputFormat instead of FileInputFormat for the same reason.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
